    {
      "title": "Intransitive Verbs (الأفعال اللازمة)",
      "titleArabic": "الأفعال اللازمة",
      "content": [
        "Intransitive verbs (الفعل اللازم) do not require a direct object to complete their meaning.",
        "These verbs express complete actions on their own, though they may be followed by prepositional phrases."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "ذَهَبَ - to go (complete meaning: ذهب الرجل)",
        "جَلَسَ - to sit (complete meaning: جلس الطالب)",
        "نَامَ - to sleep (complete meaning: نام الولد)",
        "قَامَ - to stand (complete meaning: قام المدرس)"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "ذَهَبَ الطَّالِبُ", "english": "The student went" },
        { "arabic": "جَلَسَ الرَّجُلُ", "english": "The man sat" },
        { "arabic": "نَامَتِ الْبِنْتُ", "english": "The girl slept" },
        { "arabic": "قَامَ الْمُدَرِّسُ", "english": "The teacher stood up" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Intransitive Verbs with Prepositions",
      "titleArabic": "الأفعال اللازمة مع حروف الجر",
      "content": [
        "Intransitive verbs often take prepositional phrases to provide additional information.",
        "The preposition makes the verb 'reach' its object indirectly."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "ذَهَبَ إِلَى - went to (ذهب إلى المسجد)",
        "جَلَسَ عَلَى - sat on (جلس على الكرسي)",
        "نَظَرَ إِلَى - looked at (نظر إلى السماء)",
        "دَخَلَ فِي - entered into (دخل في الغرفة)"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "ذَهَبَ الطَّالِبُ إِلَى الْمَدْرَسَةِ", "english": "The student went to the school" },
        { "arabic": "جَلَسَ الرَّجُلُ عَلَى الْكُرْسِيِّ", "english": "The man sat on the chair" },
        { "arabic": "نَظَرْتُ إِلَى السَّمَاءِ", "english": "I looked at the sky" },
        { "arabic": "دَخَلَ الضَّيْفُ فِي الْبَيْتِ", "english": "The guest entered into the house" }
      ]
    }
  ],
